FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#000000>Author</FONT><B></TD><TD valign=top><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#000000>Comment</FONT><B></FONT></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#2f2f4f><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub10.ezboard.com/bforgottentruthforeignlegion.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=dia>Dia</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_thatch.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Registered User</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#5F9EA0>9/7/00</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#5F9EA0>10:43:10 am</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT><A HREF=http://pub10.ezboard.com/fforgottentruthforeignlegiongeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=209.topic><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Reply</FONT></A></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Basics of fletching</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">For the benefit of Rayna, who wanted to know more about fletching, I'll try to stay basic.<br>
<br>
There are 3 kinds of arrows: piercing, slashing and Bludgening.<br>
<br>
Blungening arrowheads are sold in Sawato and should be use on golems,skeletons, zephirs, wasps, reedsharks and olthois.<br>
<br>
Slashing arrowheads are sold in hebian-to (broadhead) or in Baishi (more expensive, more powerful and more reliable frogs)Should be use on Undeads, zombies, lichs, revenants, sclavus, shadows.<br>
<br>
Piercings are sold everywhere and should be use with all the other nasties. The more expensive armor-piercing arrowheads are sold in Mayoi.<br>
<br>
To make greaters, use an alembic (sold in the magic shop) on quicksilver to get an infusion. Here I suggest to put your alembic in a hotkey and a bundle of 100 quicksilver in a bag or pack. Press the hot key and click the quicksilver, repeat 100 times. Then open main backpack, click one infusion and &quot;F&quot; key 50 times, drag the infusions in a hotkey and repeat. Put 100 aqua of incanta in a pack and use the infusion (using the hotkey) on the aqua. You will get oil that you should bundle and drag in a hotkey.<br>
<br>
Use the oil on arrowheads. Plain arrowheads, broads and blunts are more easily fletched than frogs and armor-piercings. Use the arrowheads on shafts and get your arrows.<br>
<br>
<br>
To get elementals, replace quicksilver by:<br>
Brimstone to get acid<br>
cobalt to get electrics<br>
colcothar to get frost<br>
turpeth to get fires<br>
<br>
I rarely use elementals, because I don't like to carry 7 kinds of arrows and they are not better then greaters. (Exept for acids on iron golems) On the otherhand, they are fletch more easily and fires works pretty good on undeads.<br>
<br>
I won't talk about greater elementals, doing those, you will end up fletching more than hunting.<br>
<br>
By the way, you can't make slashing-fires of blunt-acids, it would be too nice. And there are no better blunt-arrowheads as in slashing and piercing. I've suggested to Turbine an explosive-arrowhead... still waiting for it. Maybe in the next update!<br>
</font><P><P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#6B8E23><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub10.ezboard.com/ugharadin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Gharadin</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_ball.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Registered User</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#5F9EA0>9/7/00</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#5F9EA0>7:53:26 pm</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT><A HREF=http://pub10.ezboard.com/fforgottentruthforeignlegiongeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=209.topic&index=1><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Reply</FONT></A></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Re: Basics of fletching</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Thanks for posting this Dia, very informative! I just read a chat transcript with the developers, and they said archers should love the things they have planned over the next few months. Maybe you'll get your explosive arrowheads after all!</font><P><P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#2f2f4f><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub10.ezboard.com/ukrystl.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Krystl</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_star.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Registered User</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#5F9EA0>9/8/00</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#5F9EA0>2:35:06 am</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT><A HREF=http://pub10.ezboard.com/fforgottentruthforeignlegiongeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=209.topic&index=2><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Reply</FONT></A></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Re: Basics o